PRIVACY POLICY
This Privacy Policy describes STAR HEALTH policies and procedures on the collection, use and disclosure of our information when you use the service and informs you of your privacy rights and how the applicable law protects you. This policy is applicable to all the employees of Star Health, its suppliers, vendors, and other internal and external interested parties who have direct or indirect access to the any type of information pertaining to Star Health. At STAR HEALTH we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal data that you provide and any other information that you share with us, which allows us to provide you with the best possible experience during your visit to our website.
Earning and maintaining customer trust is core to what we do, STAR HEALTH is truly committed to transparency in our privacy practices. Any personal information disclosed to us will be processed only to the extent of your consent and we invite you to engage with us in complete trust.
We use your Personal data to provide and improve the Service. By using the Service, you consent to the collection and use of information (personal, sensitive) will be in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
This policy shall be read with STAR HEALTH website usage terms and conditions and the cookie policy due to their interconnectivity and interdependence.
Interpretation and Definitions
Interpretation
The words of which the initial letter is capitalized have meanings defined under the following conditions. The following definitions shall have the same meaning regardless of whether they appear in singular or in plural.
Definitions
For the purposes of this Privacy Policy:
Account
means a unique account created for you to access our Service or parts of our Service.
Company
(referred to as either “STAR HEALTH”, "the Company", "We", "Us" or "Our" in this Agreement) refers to Star Health & Allied Insurance Co. Pvt. Ltd.
Cookies
are small files that are placed on your computer, mobile device or any other device by a website, containing the details of your browsing history on that website among its many uses. These are also known as browser cookies or tracking cookies, they are small, often encrypted text files, located in the browser of your device(s). These cookies facilitate us in making your navigation across STAR HEALTH website smoother and personalized to perform certain functions. Due to cookies’ core role of enhancing/enabling usability or website processes, disabling cookies may prevent you from using some of our website functionalities.
Country
refers to: India and by reference means Chennai or Tamil Nadu based on context.
Device
means any device that can access the Service such as a computer, a cell phone or a digital tablet.
Personal Data
is any information that relates to an identified or identifiable natural person (i.e. you, the customer / visitor of this website) that can be used to distinguish or trace such individual’s identity, such as First Name, Last Name, Spouse Name, PAN Number, Aadhaar Number, date and place of birth, mother’s maiden name, or biometric records; and any other information that is linkable to you as an individual and not limited to information such as medical, educational, financial, and employment information. Commonly used synonyms are personal information, personally identifying information, personally identifiable information (PII) or personal/protected medical and/ or health Information (PHI).
Service
refers to the Website and is a collective term for all the services we offer on this website as you navigate through it. While all the information is free to access, we will ask you to provide us with your personal data in order for us to cater to any specific services required like payment of insurance premium or to any downloadable resources.
Service Provider
means any natural or legal person who processes the data on behalf of STAR HEALTH. It refers to third-party companies or individuals employed by STAR HEALTH to facilitate the Service, to provide the Service on behalf of the Company, to perform services related to the Service or to assist STAR HEALTH in analysing how the Service is used.
Usage Data
refers to data collected automatically, either generated by the use of the Service or from the Service infrastructure itself (for example, the duration of a page visit).
Website
refers to STAR HEALTH, accessible from
www.starhealth.in
You
mean the individual accessing or using the Service, or the company, or other legal entity on behalf of which such individual is accessing or using the Service, as applicable.
